# SQL Lookup Table Service

![FigImage](data:data:image/png;base64,)

## Description

This service communicates with the Fig lookup table API.
It can create lookup tables based on queries performed towards a third party SQL database.

See the [Fig Documentation](http://www.figsettings.com/docs/features/lookup-tables) for details on how lookup tables work.

The service can be configured with multiple expressions generating multiple lookup tables.
Note that each SQL expression must only return 2 columns, a key and a value.

## Settings

### FigUri

The base URI where the Fig API is listening.


### FigUsername

The username when logging into Fig. It is recommended that this be assigned the **LookupService** role for security reasons.


### FigPassword

The password corresponding to the username for Fig.


### RefreshIntervalMs

The interval in milliseconds between reading the database and updating Fig.


### DatabaseConnectionString

The connection string for the SQL database.


### ConnectionStringPassword

The password component of the SQL connection string (if required).
Just add {0} in the connection string in the place where the password should be located.

e.g.
```
Server=myServerAddress;User Id=myUsername;Password={0};
```


### Configuration

The lookup table configurations. The name will be used for the lookup table name.
The SQL statement must return 2 values, the first will be the key and the second the value for the lookup table.

> ℹ️ NOTE
> 
> The key must be unique.


### LogLevel

The minimum level at which to log.
